HEADWORD: Lucullite
<hw>Lu*cul"lite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<etsep>Lucullus</etsep>, a Roman consul, famous for his great wealth and
luxury: cf. F. <ets>lucullite</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A
variety of black limestone, often polished for ornamental
purposes.</def>⟦br⟧
